result.name: Sorabol Restaurant

reviews.text: Delicious authentic Korean cuisine. One star less for the restaurant being dated, the tables are very old and need an upgrade. But if you can get over that, you are in for a great meal.

Unfortunately, the food and bad customer service experience tainted the evening. AVOID at all cost. We've waited on by 5 servers chit chatting among themselves and playing around an otherwise empty restaurant. No wonder the restaurant is empty on a Sunday evenings. There were more staff than customers. We cleaned our own tables, chased for our food... and even found a cockroach in our soup.

The food there is mediocre. Not worth 120 USD for a two people course. What's worse is that the service is abismal; the waiters are not attentive, had to call them on various occasions so they could get my order (they just nod and leave without returning). They also kept forgetting simple things such as providing me with thongs to grill the meat or bowls for the stew we ordered... And they also made me pay while I was eating, which I found extremely rude. The most shocking thing is that I saw two waitresses EATING THE LEFTOVERS of another table instead of promptly servicing our table. One of the waitress' name was 'Fe'.

Food 4/5
Drink 3/5
Price 3/5
Service 3/5
Ambience 3/5
 Recommendations: beef short ribs😋
Good food, bad service, not that clean.
